Title: Director of Studies (DoS)
Description: Born and bred in Essex (Maldon then Chelmsford) who later attended a well-known international school in the Brentwood district located on the London commuter belt. Due to the experiences I had obtained there, my English and Irish relatives' (teaching) support as well as my professional development journey in the UK, Germany and in Spain, I decided to become and remain a linguist and teacher in life. I have been active in ELT and pedagogy for over fifteen years now, especially in Germany, but have also taught and examined students in other countries such as in France and in Switzerland. My key areas of interest in the profession are underpinned by ELF (English as a Lingua Franca), teaching methodologies and English phonology. My main professional goal is to share my passion for (teaching) the English language with both teachers and students. I also thoroughly enjoy working together with other trainers who teach MFLs such as German, Dutch, French and Spanish. In my free time I like to speak and practise my Irish Gaelic, go cycling, play with my two beautiful cats Oscar and Fritz and read the great wealth of material there is about ELT.

Description: Mein Name ist Wladimir Simonov, ich bin seit 2005 Versicherungsmakler und habe selbst ungefähr so ziemlich alle Fehler gemacht, die ein Unternehmer machen kann. Ich habe seit Beginn meiner Karriere... ✅So ziemlich alle bekannten Akquisemethoden ausprobiert, ✅Aus eigener Kraft und ohne fremde Unterstützung mit einem selbstentwickelten System über 1.000 Kunden in nur 4 Jahren durch Social Media gewonnen, ✅Wurde auf der DKM 2018 zum "Social Media Makler" des Jahres gekürt, ✅Und bin mittlerweile einer der gefragtesten Experten meiner Branche zu den Themen Social Media, Content Marketing und Digitalisierung geworden. Dadurch gewann ich immer mehr Einblicke in Geschäftsmodelle von erfolgreichen Unternehmern, fand Gemeinsamkeiten und optimiere damit meine Kurse, Workshops & Coachings heute noch fortlaufend. Ein Kollege bezeichnete mich mal als einen "Überzeugungstäter" und "Positiv-Bekloppten". Das beschreibt mich ziemlich treffend und deshalb bin ich sicherlich nicht für jeden der richtige Coach. Ich habe Ecken, Kanten und eine gesunde Portion Unbequemlichkeit. Du wirst mich sehr selten bis nie mit Anzug und Krawatte erleben. Mein Coaching wird niemals für alle verfügbar sein und ich werde nicht jeden Interessenten als Kunden nehmen. Wenn Du erfahren möchtest, ob Du geeignet bist, dann bewirb Dich für ein kostenloses Erstgespräch unter https://www.wladimirsimonov.de/methode

Description:
Are you a senior leader of a language school, or independent school looking to attract overseas agents and students?

Do you feel worried about reaching capacity? 

Concerned you might be over-reliant on a handful of agents or markets? Have you seen some great schools sadly shut down and are determined it won't happen to you?

Do you feel you've weathered a few storms and are wearing a few hats but making sales is slipping down the list?

Do you want to not only be at capacity for bookings but also be able to build up reserves to build up reserves (just in case)?

Would you like a solid sales function and great processes to give you consistency in sales, control of nationality mix and partners, to give you better outcomes for your students, and better reviews?

Would having someone help you see clearly what to focus on, to see what needs doing, and how long it'll take plus steps to get there, make a tangible difference to your day to day business?

If so, I can help

The Sales Health Check gives you a step-by-step set of actions that will scale your sales. It's completely bespoke to your business and designed specifically for the international education sector. With a money back guarantee, you can be confident that this will have a tangibly positive result showing on your student numbers.

I have 27  years experience in sales in international education. I'm known for being direct but kind, qualified and well connected and passionate about our sector. I've been delivering free support during these past years as I am fully invested in helping you through hard times. 

I am CPD Accredited and a Fellow of the Institute of Sales Professionals, a keynote speaker and published sales writer.

I've built my reputation on the fact that the sector trusts me to deliver in a non-judgemental but results-driven way.

Sales season starts all over again in September and you need to be ready before then with a solid sales function. The sooner you start, the better. Get your summer bills paid and ensure against uncertainty in the future. 

The Sales Health check costs £2997, takes one week, and over that week I spend time with the leadership and those involved in the sales process. The report is delivered one week later and we get together after you've had time to digest it to go over it all.

From there you can work with me on a deeper level if you'd like to, I can help you implement everything with consultancy, training, coaching or put you in touch with tech teams.

If now is the time to take control of sales in your business, send me a direct message. I’d love a chat!
